When creating a script that is not part of the main application:
- scripts/analysis - For data analysis, reporting, insights
- scripts/validations - For validators, data quality checks
- scripts/test - Manual test scripts, integration testing
- scripts/utilities - Processing scripts, integration tools, utilities
Use your judgment when creating scripts. When creating a guide, put it in docs/guides.

Scripts organization:
- scripts/analysis/ - Data analysis, reporting, insights
- scripts/validations/ - Data quality checks and correctness verification
- scripts/test/ - Manual test scripts, integration testing, debugging
- scripts/utilities/ - Processing scripts, integration tools, utilities
- scripts/results/ - Output files and reports

Test Organization:
- tests/ - Proper unit tests (pytest/unittest) with assertions, mocking, CI/CD
- scripts/test/ - Manual test scripts, integration testing, debugging tools

Clean up one-time use scripts after completion.

## No Hardcoded Secrets Rule

**NEVER commit secrets, API tokens, passwords, or credentials in code.**

- Use environment variables for all secrets
- Use `.env` files for local development (gitignored)
- Create `.env.example` templates
- Document required env vars in README

See `docs/rules/no-hardcoded-secrets.md` for complete guidelines.
